dcterms:description: This dataset contains whole-brain structural network alterations in patients with temporal lobe epilepsy (TLE) and focal to bilateral tonic-clonic seizures (FBTCS), focusing on how node abnormality predicts seizure outcomes and relates to long-term relapse after epilepsy surgery.
dcterms:title: Whole-brain structural network alterations in patients with temporal lobe epilepsy (TLE) and focal to bilateral tonic-clonic seizures (FBTCS)

dcterms:creator: P. A. Cook
M. Symms
P. A. Boulby
D. C. Alexander
dcterms:description: This dataset includes diffusion-weighted MRI data from 112 participants, comprising 60 patients with FBTCS+, 23 patients with FBTCS-, and 29 healthy controls, used to analyze brain connectivity.
dcterms:title: Diffusion-weighted MRI data from 112 participants (60 FBTCS+ patients, 23 FBTCS- patients, and 29 controls)

dcterms:creator: M. Jenkinson
C. F. Beckmann
T. E. J. Behrens
M. W. Woolrich
S. M. Smith
dcterms:description: This dataset provides connectivity matrices for FBTCS+ and FBTCS- patients, used to assess differences in brain network connectivity between these groups.
dcterms:title: Connectivity matrices for FBTCS+ and FBTCS- patients

dcterms:creator: N. Sinha

M. Kaiser
S. S. Cash
M. B. Westover
Y. Wang
dcterms:description: This dataset includes node abnormality metrics derived from structural connectivity matrices, which are used to predict neurosurgical outcomes in focal epilepsy patients.
dcterms:title: Node abnormality metrics derived from the structural connectivity matrices

dcterms:creator: B. C. Bernhardt
L. Bonilha
D. W. Gross
dcterms:description: This dataset contains abnormality load metrics for FBTCS+ and FBTCS- patients, which are used to analyze network abnormalities in epilepsy.
dcterms:title: Abnormality load metrics for FBTCS+ and FBTCS- patients
